      <p class="title"><b>PREPARATION:</b></p>
      <li><b>1.</b> Add 4 tbsp oat to half a cup of (125 ml) milk and let it sit overnight in the fridge.</li>
      <li><b>2.</b> Next day, put the oats, half a cup of (125ml) milk, beets, 3 strawberries and honey in a blender and blend.</li>
      <li><b>3.</b> Take the mixture on the serving plate. (You can add more milk according to its consistency).</li>
      <li><b>4.</b> Decorate it with a strawberry, a kiwi, plums, chia seeds, germinated wheat seed juice dessert and raw almonds.</li>
